$ Oracle: Real-time statistics gathering

Real-time statistics is the logical extends → development/databases/Oracle/optimizer/statistics/gathering/online[online statistics gathering] to
conventional → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/DML operations.

Real-time statistics was introducted with → development/databases/Oracle/Releases-and-versions/19c.

Real-time statistics is only available for → development/databases/Oracle/Exadata.

sa:

  The → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/init-parameters[init parameter] `→ development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/init-parameters/optimizer/real_time_statistics`
  controls whether Oracle gathers real-time → development/databases/Oracle/optimizer/statistics[statistics] during conventional
  → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/DML operations.
